summaries.short: Sabi encourages Violet to work through her complex emotions as the family searches for the best way to celebrate a birthday.
summaries.full: As her birthday nears and complex emotions continue to mount, Violet lands herself in deep trouble at school and is forced to work with a therapist. While Sabi helps Violet process her feelings, a traumatizing experience brings 7ven home from Berlin.

summaries.full: 7ven’s Ellen-themed costume party provides a long-overdue escape, allowing Sabi to embrace some much-needed fun. But when the kids call for help, Sabi rushes over – only for their fraught relationship with Paul to reach its breaking point.

summaries.short: Sabi makes another sacrifice in service of the family, while Paul digs deeper into Bessy’s secret. Raffo clings to her place in her child’s life, and Sabi’s ex attempts to win them back.
summaries.full: Sabi resigns from their beloved Bar Bük, making yet another sacrifice to help Bessy’s family adjust to their new normal. Meanwhile, Paul continues to pose as Bessy in texts to the mysterious Penny, Raffo attempts to understand her child’s identity, and Sabi’s ex makes a desperate play for their affection.

summaries.full: Sabi’s blissful morning surrounded by old and new friends is cut short when Aqsa forces them to help check on their mom. While visiting their childhood home, Sabi attempts to bear their truth to extended family – with less-than-ideal results. Meanwhile, finally ready to visit her own mom, Violet calls on 7ven for help.
